$ cmd.exe: set /p

`set /p` allows to have the user enter a value and assign it to a → development/environment-variable[environment variable].

The → development/line-break[new line] that → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/echo[`echo`] writes can be piped into `set /p` to
→ Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/echo#cmd-exe-no-newlines[`echo` text without new lines].


sa:
  → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/set[`set`]

  A usage of `set /p` is → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/goto#cmd-exe_let-user-choose-an-option[to let a user choose an option in a batch file].

  Other → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands[cmd.exe commands]
